About This Home

Beautifully updated Oakland home with the perfect balance of some of its original characteristics. Stunning interior paint colors, classic white wood cabinets in the kitchen with open oak shelving and brand new stainless steel appliances. Each bathroom has its own beautiful unique touches, from the vanities to the shower fixtures. Don't forget about the perfect sized backyard that is ready for summer and your personal touch! Quick freeway access and short distance to Bart. Come see this gorgeous home this weekend!

This property was built in 1900 and last sold on August 22, 2019 for $920,000. Based on Redfin's Oakland data, we estimate the home's value is $967,441, which is 1.9% more than its current list price. Comparable nearby homes include 812 37th St, 990 43 Rd St, and 908 55th. Nearby schools include St. Martin de Porres, Oakland Military Institute, College Preparatory Academy and Sat: Skinner Academic Tutoring. The closest grocery stores are Micro's Market, North Side Supermarket and Kings Market. Nearby coffee shops include Subrosa Coffee MLK, Café Dejéna and MLK Cafe. Nearby restaurants include Arthur Mac's Tap and Snack, The Kebabery and Bonsai Japanese Restaurant. 737 44th St is near Helen McGregor Plaza Park, Temescal Creek Park and Grove Shafter Park.
